{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NvX2uP86BpuY5UosbFwPgg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 12.4: Shared Test Utilities and Fixtures\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer,\n    12→I want reusable test helpers and fixtures,\n    13→So that tests don't duplicate mock setup across 50+ files.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` exists, when inspected, then it contains: `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `state-builders.ts`, `mock-factories.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` exists, when test files import from it, then common patterns (mock Docker, mock fs, create temp state) are one-liners <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, when inspected, then it exports named Cargo.toml string constants covering: minimal, actix-web, axum, async-openai, workspace, binary, library, and generic variants <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given `state-builders.ts`, when inspected, then it exports a `buildSprintState(overrides?: Partial<SprintState>): SprintState` factory that returns a valid SprintStateV2 object with sensible defaults <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given `mock-factories.ts`, when inspected, then it exports factory functions for commonly mocked modules: `createFsMock()`, `createChildProcessMock()`, `createDockerMock()`, `createStateMock()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given `helpers.ts`, when inspected, then it exports `withTempDir(fn: (dir: string) => Promise<void>)` that creates a temp directory, runs the callback, and cleans up on completion or error <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `helpers.ts`, when inspected, then it re-exports all fixtures and mock factories so consumers have a single import point <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing 3493+ tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given at least 3 existing test files are refactored to use the new shared utilities, when inspected, then their mock setup boilerplate is reduced (demonstrating the pattern works in practice) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given no file in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` or `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→\n    28→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    29→\n    30→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 3): Create `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts`\n    31→  - [x] Export named string constants for each Cargo.toml variant (minimal, actix-web, axum, async-openai, workspace, binary, library, generic)\n    32→  - [x] Extract inline Cargo.toml strings from `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/rust.test.ts` as the source of truth\n    33→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 1, 4): Create `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts`\n    34→  - [x] Import `SprintState` (aliased to `SprintStateV2`) from `src/types/state.ts`\n    35→  - [x] Export `buildSprintState(overrides?)` with sensible defaults (version 2, current date, empty stories array, etc.)\n    36→  - [x] Export `buildStoryEntry(overrides?)` for individual story objects\n    37→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 1, 5): Create `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.ts`\n    38→  - [x] `createFsMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for readFileSync, writeFileSync, existsSync, mkdirSync, etc.\n    39→  - [x] `createChildProcessMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for execFileSync, spawn, etc.\n    40→  - [x] `createDockerMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for isStackRunning, startStack, stopStack, etc.\n    41→  - [x] `createStateMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for readLocalConfig, getProjectRoot, etc.\n    42→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 2, 6, 7): Create `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`\n    43→  - [x] Export `withTempDir()` utility\n    44→  - [x] Re-export all from `./fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `./fixtures/state-builders.ts`, `./fixtures/mock-factories.ts`\n    45→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 9): Refactor at least 3 existing test files to use shared utilities\n    46→  - [x] `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/rust.test.ts` — replace inline Cargo.toml strings with fixture imports\n    47→  - [x] `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/selector.test.ts` — replace inline makeState/makeBadState with shared builders\n    48→  - [x] `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/feedback.test.ts` — replace inline mockState with state-builders\n    49→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 8): Run full test suite — all tests pass, zero regressions\n    50→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 10): Verify all new files are under 300 lines\n    51→\n    52→## Dev Notes\n    53→\n    54→### Architecture Compliance\n    55→\n    56→- **Decision 4 (Domain Subdirectories):** The architecture specifies `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` for shared test data and `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` for mock factories and state builders. Follow this exactly.\n    57→- **300-line limit (Decision 7, NFR5):** All new files must stay under 300 lines.\n    58→- **Import convention:** Test files importing shared utilities should use `import { ... } from '../../lib/__tests__/helpers.js'` (or relative equivalent). The `.js` extension is required for ESM resolution.\n    59→\n    60→### Duplication Analysis (Why This Story Matters)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jf4NVSZHxoiSr5pCRGQCHS","session_id":"8c35c2f7-0e10-4994-a438-2b5cecce3396","uuid":"57b5f334-2172-4eb8-9819-cdcf6e16f77a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:28:24.793Z"}
