{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D3RnQi6GJBeWbxodJBEF5n","type":"tool_result","content":"    60→### Duplication Analysis (Why This Story Matters)\n    61→\n    62→Current test codebase has significant duplication:\n    63→- **17 `vi.mock('node:fs', ...)` declarations** across test files\n    64→- **22 `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` declarations**\n    65→- **26 `vi.mock(...)` calls for Docker-related modules**\n    66→- **8 `vi.mock(...)` calls for state modules**\n    67→- Inline Cargo.toml string literals repeated across 14+ test assertions in `rust.test.ts`\n    68→- Each test file independently builds mock objects for the same modules\n    69→\n    70→### Testing Framework\n    71→\n    72→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n    73→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach, vi } from 'vitest'`\n    74→\n    75→### Mock Factory Design Guidance\n    76→\n    77→Mock factories should return plain objects with `vi.fn()` stubs. They should NOT call `vi.mock()` themselves — that must happen at the module level in each test file (Vitest requirement: `vi.mock()` is hoisted). The factories provide the mock implementations that test files pass to `vi.mock()`.\n    78→\n    79→Example pattern:\n    80→```typescript\n    81→// In mock-factories.ts:\n    82→export function createFsMock() {\n    83→  return {\n    84→    readFileSync: vi.fn(),\n    85→    writeFileSync: vi.fn(),\n    86→    existsSync: vi.fn(() => true),\n    87→    mkdirSync: vi.fn(),\n    88→    mkdtempSync: vi.fn(),\n    89→    rmSync: vi.fn(),\n    90→  };\n    91→}\n    92→\n    93→// In a test file:\n    94→import { createFsMock } from '../../lib/__tests__/helpers.js';\n    95→const fsMock = createFsMock();\n    96→vi.mock('node:fs', () => fsMock);\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→### State Builder Design Guidance\n   100→\n   101→The `buildSprintState()` factory must produce valid `SprintStateV2` objects. Reference `src/types/state.ts` for the interface (lines 97-127). Use `Partial<SprintState>` spread pattern for overrides.\n   102→\n   103→### Previous Story Intelligence (12-3)\n   104→\n   105→- Story 12-3 completed successfully. Pattern: extract from monolith into domain module, keep thin command layer.\n   106→- 3493 tests passing as of story 12-3 completion.\n   107→- Coverage: 97.09% overall, all 150 files above 80% per-file floor.\n   108→- Import boundaries test (`src/modules/__tests__/import-boundaries.test.ts`) enforces module isolation.\n   109→\n   110→### Refactoring Guidance\n   111→\n   112→When refactoring existing test files (Task 5), the approach is:\n   113→1. Import the shared utility\n   114→2. Replace the inline mock/fixture with the shared version\n   115→3. Run the specific test file to verify no regressions\n   116→4. Do NOT change test logic or assertions — only the mock setup\n   117→\n   118→### Project Structure Notes\n   119→\n   120→Target file tree after this story:\n   121→```\n   122→src/lib/__tests__/\n   123→  fixtures/\n   124→    cargo-toml-variants.ts   # Named Cargo.toml string constants\n   125→    state-builders.ts         # buildSprintState(), buildStoryEntry()\n   126→    mock-factories.ts         # createFsMock(), createChildProcessMock(), etc.\n   127→  helpers.ts                  # withTempDir(), re-exports all fixtures\n   128→  ... existing test files ...\n   129→```\n   130→\n   131→### References\n   132→\n   133→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md lines 273-275] — `src/lib/__tests__/` structure spec\n   134→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 237-251] — Story 12-4 epic definition\n   135→- [Source: src/types/state.ts lines 97-131] — SprintStateV2 interface definition\n   136→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-move-status-logic-to-module.md] — Previous story learnings\n   137→\n   138→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   139→## Verification Requirements\n   140→\n   141→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.proof.md`)\n   142→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   143→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   144→\n   145→## Documentation Requirements\n   146→\n   147→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   148→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md`\n   149→\n   150→## Testing Requirements\n   151→\n   152→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   153→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   154→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   155→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   156→\n   157→## Dev Agent Record\n   158→\n   159→### Agent Model Used\n   160→\n   161→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   162→\n   163→### Debug Log References\n   164→\n   165→### Completion Notes List\n   166→\n   167→- Task 1: Created `cargo-toml-variants.ts` with 8 named Cargo.toml string constants (74 lines)\n   168→- Task 2: Created `state-builders.ts` with `buildSprintState`, `buildStoryEntry`, `buildEpicState`, `buildActionItem`, `buildSprintStateWithStory` (139 lines)\n   169→- Task 3: Created `mock-factories.ts` with `createFsMock`, `createChildProcessMock`, `createDockerMock`, `createStateMock` (96 lines)\n   170→- Task 4: Created `helpers.ts` with `withTempDir()` and re-exports of all fixtures (37 lines)\n   171→- Task 5: Refactored 3 test files: rust.test.ts (11 inline Cargo.toml strings replaced), feedback.test.ts (2 inline SprintState objects replaced), selector.test.ts (makeState/makeBadState replaced with shared builders). Note: docker.test.ts was originally targeted but replaced with selector.test.ts because `vi.mock()` hoisting prevents using factory imports inside `vi.mock()` callbacks — the mock factory pattern is most useful for mock *configuration* (return values), not `vi.mock()` declarations themselves.\n   172→- Task 6: Full test suite passes — 3539 tests across 134 files, zero regressions (up from 3493 due to 46 new tests)\n   173→- Task 7: All new files under 300 lines (max: 139 lines for state-builders.ts)\n   174→\n   175→### Change Log\n   176→\n   177→- 2026-03-24: Story 12-4 implemented — shared test utilities and fixtures\n   178→- 2026-03-24: Code review fixes — removed phantom functions (readLocalConfig, getProjectRoot) from createStateMock; split into createStateMock + createSprintStateMock; removed unused StoryStatus import from state-builders.ts; updated tests and AGENTS.md\n   179→\n   180→### File List\n   181→\n   182→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts (new)\n   183→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts (new)\n   184→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.ts (new)\n   185→- src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts (new)\n   186→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.test.ts (new)\n   187→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.test.ts (new)\n   188→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.test.ts (new)\n   189→- src/lib/__tests__/helpers.test.ts (new)\n   190→- src/lib/__tests__/stacks/rust.test.ts (modified)\n   191→- src/modules/sprint/__tests__/feedback.test.ts (modified)\n   192→- src/modules/sprint/__tests__/selector.test.ts (modified)\n   193→- src/lib/AGENTS.md (modified)\n   194→- docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md (new)\n   195→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jf4NVSZHxoiSr5pCRGQCHS","session_id":"8c35c2f7-0e10-4994-a438-2b5cecce3396","uuid":"250769d1-4a0b-4be6-a523-24ed5bb04cb2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:28:49.922Z"}
