{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U9Q8fdpAxi2DnSHxo6NqQ3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-1: Create AgentDriver Interface and Types\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want an `AgentDriver` interface that abstracts agent execution,\n     9→So that Ralph can be replaced or supplemented without touching 28 files.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/agents/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it defines `AgentDriver`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given the `AgentEvent` type, when inspected, then it covers: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction).** Define the contract that any agent implementation must fulfill.\n    19→\n    20→The full type definitions (from architecture-v3.md):\n    21→\n    22→```typescript\n    23→// src/lib/agents/types.ts\n    24→interface AgentDriver {\n    25→  readonly name: string;\n    26→  spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess;\n    27→  parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null;\n    28→  getStatusFile(): string;\n    29→}\n    30→\n    31→interface SpawnOpts {\n    32→  storyKey: string;\n    33→  prompt: string;\n    34→  workDir: string;\n    35→  timeout: number;\n    36→  env?: Record<string, string>;\n    37→}\n    38→\n    39→interface AgentProcess {\n    40→  stdout: Readable;\n    41→  stderr: Readable;\n    42→  on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void;\n    43→  kill(signal?: string): void;\n    44→}\n    45→\n    46→type AgentEvent =\n    47→  | { type: 'tool-start'; name: string }\n    48→  | { type: 'tool-complete'; name: string; args: string }\n    49→  | { type: 'text'; text: string }\n    50→  | { type: 'story-complete'; key: string; details: string }\n    51→  | { type: 'story-failed'; key: string; reason: string }\n    52→  | { type: 'iteration'; count: number }\n    53→  | { type: 'retry'; attempt: number; delay: number }\n    54→  | { type: 'result'; cost: number; sessionId: string };\n    55→```\n    56→\n    57→This is a types-only story. No implementation code beyond the interface definitions and the `index.ts` re-export facade.\n    58→\n    59→The `AgentProcess` interface wraps Node.js `ChildProcess` but abstracts it so future drivers (direct API calls, WebSocket connections) can implement it differently.\n    60→\n    61→`AgentEvent` is a discriminated union on `type`. The `parseOutput()` method converts raw agent output lines into typed events. Each driver knows its own output format.\n    62→\n    63→Also create the `src/lib/agents/index.ts` facade that will later re-export the driver registry.\n    64→\n    65→## Files to Change\n    66→\n    67→- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — Create. Define `AgentDriver`, `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` interfaces and types\n    68→- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Create. Re-export types. Will later re-export driver registry and implementations\n    69→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jf4NVSZHxoiSr5pCRGQCHS","session_id":"8c35c2f7-0e10-4994-a438-2b5cecce3396","uuid":"dd3c87f1-a742-473f-96d8-cffe4d1592c3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:28:54.362Z"}
