{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AZbeiVjr5UDEKGpida9WkD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-1: Create AgentDriver Interface and Types\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer,\n    12→I want an `AgentDriver` interface that abstracts agent execution,\n    13→So that Ralph can be replaced or supplemented without touching 28 files.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given `src/lib/agents/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it exports `AgentDriver`, `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given the `AgentDriver` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `readonly name: string`, `spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess`, `parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null`, `getStatusFile(): string` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given the `SpawnOpts` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `storyKey: string`, `prompt: string`, `workDir: string`, `timeout: number`, `env?: Record<string, string>` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given the `AgentProcess` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `stdout: Readable`, `stderr: Readable`, `on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void`, `kill(signal?: string): void` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given the `AgentEvent` type, when inspected, then it is a discriminated union on `type` covering: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given `src/lib/agents/index.ts` exists, when inspected, then it re-exports all types from `./types.js` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given no file in `src/lib/agents/`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` exists, when inspected, then it verifies the type exports are importable and the `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→\n    28→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    29→\n    30→- [ ] Task 1 (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5): Create `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n    31→  - [ ] Define and export `SpawnOpts` interface with `storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env?`\n    32→  - [ ] Import `Readable` from `node:stream`\n    33→  - [ ] Define and export `AgentProcess` interface with `stdout`, `stderr`, `on('close')`, `kill()`\n    34→  - [ ] Define and export `AgentEvent` discriminated union type with all 8 event types\n    35→  - [ ] Define and export `AgentDriver` interface with `name`, `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`\n    36→- [ ] Task 2 (AC: 6): Create `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n    37→  - [ ] Re-export all types from `./types.js`\n    38→  - [ ] Add placeholder comment for future driver registry and implementations\n    39→- [ ] Task 3 (AC: 10): Create `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`\n    40→  - [ ] Verify all type exports are importable from the module\n    41→  - [ ] Verify `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types via type-level tests\n    42→  - [ ] Verify `AgentDriver` interface shape matches specification\n    43→- [ ] Task 4 (AC: 7): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    44→- [ ] Task 5 (AC: 8): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    45→- [ ] Task 6 (AC: 9): Verify all new files are under 300 lines\n    46→\n    47→## Dev Notes\n    48→\n    49→### Architecture Compliance\n    50→\n    51→- **Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction):** This story creates the foundational types from architecture-v3.md Decision 3. The `AgentDriver` interface is the contract that `RalphDriver` (story 13-2) and future drivers must implement.\n    52→- **Decision 4 (Domain Subdirectories):** Files go under `src/lib/agents/` per the architecture's target file tree.\n    53→- **300-line limit (Decision 7, NFR5):** All new files must stay under 300 lines. This is a types-only story so files will be well under the limit.\n    54→\n    55→### Implementation Guidance\n    56→\n    57→This is a **types-only story**. No implementation code beyond interface definitions and the `index.ts` re-export facade.\n    58→\n    59→The `AgentProcess` interface wraps Node.js `ChildProcess` but abstracts it so future drivers (direct API calls, WebSocket connections) can implement it differently. Import `Readable` from `node:stream` for the stream types.\n    60→\n    61→`AgentEvent` is a discriminated union on `type`. The `parseOutput()` method converts raw agent output lines into typed events. Each driver knows its own output format.\n    62→\n    63→All types should be `export`ed (not `export default`) so they can be individually imported.\n    64→\n    65→### Type Design Notes\n    66→\n    67→```typescript\n    68→// src/lib/agents/types.ts\n    69→import type { Readable } from 'node:stream';\n    70→\n    71→export interface SpawnOpts {\n    72→  storyKey: string;\n    73→  prompt: string;\n    74→  workDir: string;\n    75→  timeout: number;\n    76→  env?: Record<string, string>;\n    77→}\n    78→\n    79→export interface AgentProcess {\n    80→  stdout: Readable;\n    81→  stderr: Readable;\n    82→  on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void;\n    83→  kill(signal?: string): void;\n    84→}\n    85→\n    86→export type AgentEvent =\n    87→  | { type: 'tool-start'; name: string }\n    88→  | { type: 'tool-complete'; name: string; args: string }\n    89→  | { type: 'text'; text: string }\n    90→  | { type: 'story-complete'; key: string; details: string }\n    91→  | { type: 'story-failed'; key: string; reason: string }\n    92→  | { type: 'iteration'; count: number }\n    93→  | { type: 'retry'; attempt: number; delay: number }\n    94→  | { type: 'result'; cost: number; sessionId: string };\n    95→\n    96→export interface AgentDriver {\n    97→  readonly name: string;\n    98→  spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess;\n    99→  parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null;\n   100→  getStatusFile(): string;\n   101→}\n   102→```\n   103→\n   104→### Testing Guidance\n   105→\n   106→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   107→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'`\n   108→- For a types-only story, tests verify that types are importable and that the discriminated union shape is correct. Use type-level assertions and runtime checks on type guard functions if applicable.\n   109→- Import convention: use `.js` extension for ESM resolution (e.g., `from '../types.js'`).\n   110→\n   111→### Previous Story Intelligence (12-4)\n   112→\n   113→- Story 12-4 completed successfully. All 3539 tests passing.\n   114→- Import boundaries test (`src/modules/__tests__/import-boundaries.test.ts`) enforces module isolation.\n   115→- Shared test utilities available at `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`.\n   116→\n   117→### Project Structure After This Story\n   118→\n   119→```\n   120→src/lib/agents/\n   121→├── types.ts          # AgentDriver, SpawnOpts, AgentProcess, AgentEvent\n   122→├── index.ts          # Re-export facade\n   123→└── __tests__/\n   124→    └── types.test.ts # Type import verification tests\n   125→```\n   126→\n   127→### References\n   128→\n   129→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md lines 173-213] — Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction) full specification\n   130→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 255-273] — Story 13-1 epic definition\n   131→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md] — Previous story learnings\n   132→\n   133→## Files to Change\n   134→\n   135→- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — Create. Define `AgentDriver`, `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` interfaces and types\n   136→- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Create. Re-export types. Will later re-export driver registry and implementations\n   137→- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` — Create. Type import and shape verification tests\n   138→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nff8CRPRjaDuHBnM4sLje2","session_id":"8c35c2f7-0e10-4994-a438-2b5cecce3396","uuid":"dc12d46c-852f-4799-88af-db1b31f76991","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:32:52.588Z"}
