{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cvx7QttoPt7CA5UwMXA9Bq","type":"tool_result","content":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-127-}\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-128-```\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-129-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md:130:### Decision 3: Runtime Validation — Verification IS the Runtime Check\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-131-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-132-**Decision:** Runtime observability validation happens DURING black-box verification, not as a separate step. Every user interaction with the software during verification must produce at least one log entry in the observability stack.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-133-\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-315-| FR | Module | Decision |\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-316-|----|--------|----------|\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-317-| FR1-5 | observability/ | Decision 1 (Semgrep), Decision 2 (separate metrics) |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md:318:| FR6-9 | observability/ | Decision 3 (module-level matching) |\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-319-| FR10-12 | observability/ | Decision 2 (separate metrics, enforcement via hooks) |\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-320-| FR13-21 | audit/ | Decision 4 (coordinator pattern) |\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md-321-| FR22-25 | infra/ | Decision 5 (rules as markdown) |\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-226-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-227-**Rationale:** v1's critical failure was that flags were never set. The CLI exposes `codeharness state set <key> <value>` as a subcommand. Hooks call it. The agent calls it. No more \"flags hardcoded false forever.\"\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-228-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md:229:### Decision 3: Beads Integration\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-230-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-231-**Decision:** Beads is the unified task store. CLI wraps `bd` commands. Two-layer model: beads = status/ordering, story files = content.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-232-\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-442-    labels: [\"user-retro\", \"auto-filed\"]\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-443-```\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-444-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md:445:**Rationale:** Beads remains the universal store (per Decision 3). GitHub issues are an external source/destination, not a replacement for beads. The `retro_issue_targets` config makes cross-project issue creation pluggable without hardcoding repos.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md-446-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/arch