{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WRcThy9FyMjn36zSjVQY2r","type":"tool_result","content":"163-**To:**\n164-```typescript\n165-const provider = getStackProvider(stack);\n166-provider.detectCoverageConfig(dir);\n167-```\n168-\n169-**Multi-stack:** `detectStacks()` stays in `registry.ts`. Returns `StackDetection[]`. Each detection carries a reference to its provider.\n170-\n171----\n172-\n173:### Decision 3: Agent Abstraction — Ralph Becomes One Implementation\n174-\n175-**Problem:** 28 files reference Ralph directly. State files are written by bash, read by TypeScript. No versioned contract. If Ralph is replaced, 28 files break.\n176-\n177:**Decision:** Create an `AgentDriver` interface. Ralph becomes one implementation. Future drivers (direct Claude API, other LLM CLIs) can be added.\n178-\n179-```typescript\n180-// src/lib/agents/types.ts\n181:interface AgentDriver {\n182-  readonly name: string;\n183-  spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess;\n184-  parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null;\n185-  getStatusFile(): string;\n186-}\n187-\n188-interface AgentProcess {\n189-  stdout: Readable;\n190-  stderr: Readable;\n191-  on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void;\n--\n199-  | { type: 'story-complete'; key: string; details: string }\n200-  | { type: 'story-failed'; key: string; reason: string }\n201-  | { type: 'iteration'; count: number }\n202-  | { type: 'retry'; attempt: number; delay: number }\n203-  | { type: 'result'; cost: number; sessionId: string };\n204-```\n205-\n206-**File structure:**\n207-```\n208-src/lib/agents/\n209:├── types.ts          # AgentDriver, AgentProcess, AgentEvent interfaces\n210:├── ralph.ts          # RalphDriver implements AgentDriver (wraps ralph.sh)\n211-├── stream-parser.ts  # Moved from src/lib/ — parses Claude stream-json\n212-└── __tests__/\n213-```\n214-\n215-**What changes:**\n216:- `run.ts` imports `AgentDriver` instead of directly spawning ralph\n217-- `run-helpers.ts`